cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.MA, cs.DS

This paper deals with logic and game theory, specifically extending Alternating-time Temporal Logic (ATL) to include a new operator. This fits well within the scope of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as both fields involve the study of formal logic and reasoning. Additionally, the paper deals with game theory and strategic ability, which suggests that it could also fit within cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
